translated:
Kempe, Karl Gunnar, lawyer, Gothenburg, born on 10th November 1896 in Bjurholm, Västerbotten. Son of physician Sven K. and Anna Olofsson. Married on 29th with Hjördis Lindskog. Children: Ragnhild (born in 1932), Gunilla (born in 1935). 
- Completed secondary school in Skara in 1916, graduated with a law degree from Uppsala University in 1922. 
- Served as a judge in the districts of Tveta, Vista, and Mo from 1921 to 1924, as well as in the Västerbygden Water Court from 1925 to 1927. 
- Assistant lawyer at Lemchen & Nordström's Law Firm in Jönköping from 1927 to 1929, after which he established his own law practice, first in Värnamo and currently in Gothenburg. 
- In Värnamo, he held positions such as chairman of the building committee and representative at the Skånska Bank branch. 
- Member of the Swedish Lawyers Association since 1934.
